Flight Performance in Washington D.C 2019

¶

Have you ever experienced delay flights? How long time you waited at the airport? Do you know what may caused delays, and impacted your schedules? This project will dive into the aviation data, analyze on-time performance of the flights depatured from Washington,D.C in 2019. This project also will analyze delays reasons, and create a future prediction model, and provide a fight recommandation at the end.¶

Content¶

  • Overview of flight performance of D.C airports in 2019
  • Overview of flight performance by airlines
  • Delayed time comparision by airlines
  • Delay reasons
  • Analyze delay reason with worst airline
  • Delay prediction with logstic regression model

Data Sources¶

  • Bureau of Transportation Statistics
  • https://www.transtats.bts.gov/DL_SelectFields.asp
  • Coordinates data
  • https://simplemaps.com/data/us-cities

Datasets¶

  • At least 200K rows, 47 variables
  • multiple lookup tables

In 2019, there are 28.9% of flights departured from Washington D.C got delayed, and 2.12% flights got canceled.¶

Overview Flights Performance By Airlines in 2019¶

In [987]:
fig = px.bar(Num_flights_by_airline, x = 'airline', y =['count','delay','canceled'],
            title = 'Overview Flights Performance By Airlines in 2019')

PSA airline had most delayed and canceled flgihts compare to the rest airlines. In total, Southwest company has less flights against Mesa airline, but Southwest had higher number of delays in 2019. There are multiple airlines did not have any canceled flights such as Alaska, and Endeavor.¶

The relationship between Taxi-Out Time and NAS Delay¶

As we mentioned earlier, heavy traffic could cause NAS delay. Here let's see if taxi-out time affects NAS delay. As we expected, when taxi-out time increases, the delay time increases as well. The range of taxi-out time is smaller than the range of daley time, so taxi-out is not the only reason to cause delay time increased.¶

Prediction¶

After analyzing flights formance and delay reasons, now let's build a logstic regression model to predict future flights delay. In this model, I applied machine learning Keras application, and divided original dataset into training data, testing (20%) and validation data (20%).¶

import numpy as np
prediction['Delay'] = np.where((prediction['DEP_DELAY_GROUP'].notnull()) & 
                                       (prediction['DEP_DELAY_GROUP'] != -1) & 
                                       (prediction['DEP_DELAY_GROUP'] != -2) & 
                                       (prediction['DEP_DELAY_NEW'] != 0) & 
                                       (prediction['CANCELLED'] != 1),1,0)

#one-hot encoded cateogry variables 
dummy_fields = ['OP_UNIQUE_CARRIER','ORIGIN_CITY_NAME','ORIGIN_STATE_ABR',
               'DEST_CITY_NAME','DEST_STATE_ABR','CANCELLATION_CODE',
               'Description','DIV_ARR_DELAY','DIV1_AIRPORT']
for each in dummy_fields:
    dummies = pd.get_dummies(prediction[each],prefix=each,drop_first=False)
    prediction = pd.concat([prediction,dummies],axis=1)

After training the model , the model accuracy is 82% on testing data. From the confusion matrix, we could see that there are 31791 flights got delayed, and 2699 flights on time in real life, and the model got those predictions correct. But the model still mistaken 7288 fligts' status. Overall, this model is a good model for future prediction.¶

Conclusion¶

In 2019, there are almost 1/3 flights got delayed in Washington D.C area. Alaska airline has the lowest avgerage waiting time for the delayed flights, and Frontier has the highest waiting time. The airlines PSA and United got most delays with multiple reasons. After 3pm, airports will have heavy traffic volume, its high chace to get delayed by taking later afternoon flights. Taxi-out time has minor impacts on delay time, and flight distance does cause delays. If you are planning to travel soon, I would recommond you to have an vacation in spring time, take an airplan before the late afternoon time, and choose other airline instead of United and PSA. Therefore, you will have much lower chance to get delayed.¶
